# R vs. Python {#sec-r-python}

My take on the R vs Python debate is that they work better as complimentary tools rather than setting them up as competitors. In data science, you must use the tools available to you, and it is better to use the strengths of multiple tools rather than just one. So, the take here is, it is better to complimentarily use R and Python. While R is mainly for statistical programming, python is versatile. Python uses a general-purpose language that makes it a top choice within computer science. R is more for data structuring and creating customized visualizations. Quarto serves as a pipeline within coding languages, allowing them to effectively collaborate no matter the coding language. Since in Quarto you can mix code from differentiating languages, it allows for language-agnostic collaboration. Quarto also allows for workflows that are simple making it reproducible and accessible across work teams.

